        <div class="container">
            <!-- Introduction Section -->
            <section class="section">
                <h2>Welcome to KCCA</h2>
                <p>The Kampala Capital City Authority (KCCA) is the governing body of Kampala, the capital city of Uganda. Established under the Kampala Capital City Act of 2010, KCCA is responsible for the administration and development of Uganda's vibrant capital city.</p>
                
                <p>Our mandate encompasses urban planning, service delivery, infrastructure development, and ensuring sustainable growth while preserving the cultural heritage of Kampala. We work tirelessly to create a city that is not only beautiful and functional but also inclusive and prosperous for all its residents.</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Mission & Vision -->
            <section class="section">
                <h2>Our Mission & Vision</h2>
                <div class="mission-vision">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h4>Our Mission</h4>
                        <p>To transform Kampala into a attractive, secure, and environmentally sustainable city with a robust infrastructure and services that support socio-economic development for all.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h4>Our Vision</h4>
                        <p>A world-class, vibrant, and inclusive capital city that serves as the economic and cultural hub of East Africa, offering high quality of life to all its residents.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h4>Our Values</h4>
                        <p>Integrity, Accountability, Innovation, Teamwork, and Customer Focus guide our operations and service delivery to the people of Kampala.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- History -->
            <section class="section">
                <h2>Our History</h2>
                <p>Kampala's governance has evolved significantly over the years. The transformation from Kampala City Council to Kampala Capital City Authority marked a new era in urban governance and service delivery.</p>
                
                <div class="timeline">
                    <div class="timeline-item">
                        <div class="timeline-content">
                            <h4>2010</h4>
                            <p>Kampala Capital City Authority established by Act of Parliament, replacing Kampala City Council</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="timeline-item">
                        <div class="timeline-content">
                            <h4>2011</h4>
                            <p>First Executive Director appointed, marking the beginning of transformative leadership</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="timeline-item">
                        <div class="timeline-content">
                            <h4>2015</h4>
                            <p>Launch of the Kampala Physical Development Plan to guide sustainable urban growth</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="timeline-item">
                        <div class="timeline-content">
                            <h4>2020</h4>
                            <p>Implementation of major infrastructure projects including road networks and public spaces</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

